## canvas — L1 engine for the Ruxen GUI stack.
##
## Cross-platform windowing, input, and a Skia-backed 2D canvas, exposed
## *upward only* to the L2 framework (`quiver`). This is the ONLY layer of
## the GUI stack permitted to use `unsafe` / C FFI / platform-specific code
## (see `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`).
##
## Status: Milestone 1 implemented over a real Skia raster backend (with a
## deterministic software-raster fallback) in `runtime/skia_shim.c`. The FFI
## surface is grown method-by-method following the incremental-FFI discipline
## in `docs/FFI.md`; the L2 `Canvas` API is designed against the full intended
## surface from day one while L1 fills in coverage over time.
##
## The package is split across sibling files in this directory (all share one
## package namespace — no imports needed):
##
##   color.rx     — `Color` value type
##   rect.rx      — `Rect` value type
##   status.rx    — `Rxc` status-code predicates shared with the C shim
##   raw_host.rx  — `RawHost`, the FFI `lib` declarations (step 2 of docs/FFI.md)
##   canvas.rx    — `Canvas`, the drawing surface (the main upward API)
##   event.rx     — `Event`, the input/lifecycle stream
##   window.rx    — `Window`, the canvas-backed window + live OS window control
